The Islamic State in West Africa Province (ISWAP) fighters on Wednesday attacked a village near Chibok Local Government Area of Borno State, Daily Independent learned. According to a source who spoke to Daily Trust, the terrorists invaded Kautukari village, some 15 kilometres away from Chibok town, shooting sporadically and setting houses on fire The vigilante source added that the military forward operation base (FOB) in Kada, just 2km away from Kautukari, has been dislodged. -Advertisement- “They came in this night through the nearby desert, shooting from all angles, they are currently in Kautukari village, ward under Chibok council. “All the villagers and soldiers ran into the bush; some are in Chibok town now,” the source said. The attack happened hours after United Nations Secretary-General, Antonio Guterres, paid his first visit to Nigeria. Guterres arrived in Maiduguri, Borno capital, on Tuesday afternoon as part of his 2-day official visit to Nigeria. He interfaced with Governor Babagana Zulum and surrendered Boko Haram fighters and victims of insurgency. POLL Guterres, who had earlier visited the Niger Republic, will conclude his Ramadan solidarity visit to Africa with a trip to Senegal.